HEADWORD: Cavendish
<hw>Cav"en*dish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Leaf tobacco
softened, sweetened, and pressed into plugs or cakes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cut cavendish</b></col>, <cd>the plugs cut into long
shreds for smoking.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cavern</ent>⟦br⟧
